{"color": "green", "emoji": "\ud83d\udcac", "event_type": "Agent Message", "message": "I have enough context to lay out the implementation. I\u2019m going to add a durable composition interruption queue in the backend, make the worker consume requests at safe checkpoints, surface that state through the session snapshot, then ti...", "raw_event": {"item": {"id": "item_47", "text": "I have enough context to lay out the implementation. I\u2019m going to add a durable composition interruption queue in the backend, make the worker consume requests at safe checkpoints, surface that state through the session snapshot, then tighten the composition UI/tests so the user sees whether writing is pausing, waiting, or redirecting.\n\nPlan:\n1. Add persistence and model/view support for composition interruption requests.\n2. Refactor `CompositionJobService` so pause/resume/redirect become deterministic requests plus worker-side application logic.\n3. Update routes and session hydration/event handling to return the new interruption state and preserve replayability.\n4. Update composition UI copy and controls to explain pending interruption handling and in-flight behavior.\n5. Add backend and frontend tests, run targeted suites, run broader checks, then do browser-based visual verification through Docker Compose.\n6. Commit a checkpoint once the backend path is stable, then a final checkpoint after UI and verification.", "type": "agent_message"}, "type": "item.completed"}, "task_display_context": {"event_number": 91, "prompt_index": 66, "prompt_name": "65 \u2014 Interrupt, Pause, and Redirect Composition via Chat or UI", "prompt_total": 100}, "timestap": "2026-04-02T09:02:20-07:00"}
